1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/sarkariyojana.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/list-schemes-initiatives-union-budget-2018-19-central-govt-5.jpg?resize=224%2C92&amp;ssl=1 224w, https://i2.wp.com/sarkariyojana.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/list-schemes-initiatives-union-budget-2018-19-central-govt-5.jpg?resize=350%2C144&amp;ssl=1 350w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\"/></noscript><p id=\"caption-attachment-8100\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">List Schemes Initiatives Union Budget 2018-19 Central Govt Infrastructure Development</p></div><li><b>Railways / Rail Budget 2018-19</b> &#8211;<ul><li>This year, Rail Budget is increased to Rs. 1.48 lakh crore from previous Rs. 1.31 lakh crore.</li><li>Subsequently, central govt. will eliminate 4267 unmanned railway crossing in upcoming 2 years.</li><li>Accordingly, all the railway stations which has more than 25000 footfalls will now have escalators.</li></ul></li><div id=\"attachment_8101\" style=\"width: 605px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8101\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/sarkariyojana.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/list-schemes-initiatives-union-budget-2018-19-central-govt-6.jpg?resize=595%2C247&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"List Schemes Initiatives Union Budget 2018-19 Central Govt Railways\" width=\"595\" height=\"247\" class=\"size-full wp-image-8101 jetpack-lazy-image\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/sarkariyojana.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/list-schemes-initiatives-union-budget-2018-19-central-govt-6.jpg?w=595&amp;ssl=1 595w, https://i0.wp.com/sarkariyojana.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/list-schemes-initiatives-union-budget-2018-19-central-govt-6.jpg?resize=300%2C125&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/sarkariyojana.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/list-schemes-initiatives-union-budget-2018-19-central-govt-6.jpg?resize=224%2C92&amp;ssl=1 224w, https://i0.wp.com/sarkariyojana.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/list-schemes-initiatives-union-budget-2018-19-central-govt-6.jpg?resize=350%2C144&amp;ssl=1 350w\" data-lazy-sizes=\"(max-width: 595px) 100vw, 595px\" data-lazy-src=\"https://i0.wp.com/sarkariyojana.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/list-schemes-initiatives-union-budget-2018-19-central-govt-6.jpg?resize=595%2C247&amp;is-pending-load=1#038;ssl=1\" srcset=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\"><noscript><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8101\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/sarkariyojana.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/list-schemes-initiatives-union-budget-2018-19-central-govt-6.jpg?resize=595%2C247&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"List Schemes Initiatives Union Budget 2018-19 Central Govt Railways\" width=\"595\" height=\"247\" class=\"size-full wp-image-8101\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/sarkariyojana.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/list-schemes-initiatives-union-budget-2018-19-central-govt-6.jpg?w=595&amp;ssl=1 595w, https://i0.wp.com/sarkariyojana.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/list-schemes-initiatives-union-budget-2018-19-central-govt-6.jpg?resize=300%2C125&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/sarkariyojana.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/list-schemes-initiatives-union-budget-2018-19-central-govt-6.jpg?resize=224%2C92&amp;ssl=1 224w, https://i0.wp.com/sarkariyojana.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/list-schemes-initiatives-union-budget-2018-19-central-govt-6.jpg?resize=350%2C144&amp;ssl=1 350w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 595px) 100vw, 595px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\"/></noscript><p id=\"caption-attachment-8101\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">List Schemes Initiatives Union Budget 2018-19 Central Govt Railways</p></div><li><b>Aviation / Airways Sector</b> &#8211;<ul><li>Central govt. focuses on increasing the capacity of airports and to increase round trips to 5 times i.e 1 billion trips per annum.</li><li>For this purpose, central govt. has allocated Rs. 60 crore for its launch.</li><li>Furthermore, UDAN Scheme (Ude Desh ke Aam Nagrik Yojana) will connect 64 unconnected aiports across the country.</li></ul></li><div id=\"attachment_8102\" style=\"width: 561px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8102\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/sarkariyojana.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/list-schemes-initiatives-union-budget-2018-19-central-govt-7.jpg?resize=551%2C243&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"List Schemes Initiatives Union Budget 2018-19 Central Govt Airways\" width=\"551\" height=\"243\" class=\"size-full wp-image-8102 jetpack-lazy-image\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/sarkariyojana.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/list-schemes-initiatives-union-budget-2018-19-central-govt-7.jpg?w=551&amp;ssl=1 551w, https://i0.wp.com/sarkariyojana.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/list-schemes-initiatives-union-budget-2018-19-central-govt-7.jpg?resize=300%2C132&amp;ssl=1 300w\" data-lazy-sizes=\"(max-width: 551px) 100vw, 551px\" data-lazy-src=\"https://i0.wp.com/sarkariyojana.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/list-schemes-initiatives-union-budget-2018-19-central-govt-7.jpg?resize=551%2C243&amp;is-pending-load=1#038;ssl=1\" srcset=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\"><noscript><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8102\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/sarkariyojana.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/list-schemes-initiatives-union-budget-2018-19-central-govt-7.jpg?resize=551%2C243&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"List Schemes Initiatives Union Budget 2018-19 Central Govt Airways\" width=\"551\" height=\"243\" class=\"size-full wp-image-8102\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/sarkariyojana.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/list-schemes-initiatives-union-budget-2018-19-central-govt-7.jpg?w=551&amp;ssl=1 551w, https://i0.wp.com/sarkariyojana.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/list-schemes-initiatives-union-budget-2018-19-central-govt-7.jpg?resize=300%2C132&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 551px) 100vw, 551px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\"/></noscript><p id=\"caption-attachment-8102\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">List Schemes Initiatives Union Budget 2018-19 Central Govt Airways</p></div><li><b>Tax &#038; Senior Citizens</b> &#8211;<ul><li>There is no change in the personal income tax slab rates.</li><li>Central govt. has extended the existing limit of Rs. 7.5 lakh per senior citizen to Rs. 15 lakh under Pradhan Mantri Vaya Vandana Yojana (PMVVY). This scheme is extended till March 2020.<li><li>Moreover, there is standard deduction of Rs. 40,000 for medical expenses to the salaried class.</li><li>In addition to this, govt. will exempt Rs. 50,000 for medical insurance to Senior Citizens.</li><li>Furthermore, Senior Citizens will get Rs. 10,000 exemption income from FDs.</li></ul></li><div id=\"attachment_8103\" style=\"width: 567px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8103\" src=\"https://i2.wp.com/sarkariyojana.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/list-schemes-initiatives-union-budget-2018-19-central-govt-8.jpg?resize=557%2C256&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"List Schemes Initiatives Union Budget 2018-19 Central Govt Tax Senior Citizens\" width=\"557\" height=\"256\" class=\"size-full wp-image-8103 jetpack-lazy-image\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://i2.wp.com/sarkariyojana.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/list-schemes-initiatives-union-budget-2018-19-central-govt-8.jpg?w=557&amp;ssl=1 557w, https://i2.wp.com/sarkariyojana.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/list-schemes-initiatives-union-budget-2018-19-central-govt-8.jpg?resize=300%2C138&amp;ssl=1 300w\" data-lazy-sizes=\"(max-width: 557px) 100vw, 557px\" data-lazy-src=\"https://i2.wp.com/sarkariyojana.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/list-schemes-initiatives-union-budget-2018-19-central-govt-8.jpg?resize=557%2C256&amp;is-pending-load=1#038;ssl=1\" srcset=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\"><noscript><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-8103\" src=\"https://i2.wp.com/sarkariyojana.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/list-schemes-initiatives-union-budget-2018-19-central-govt-8.jpg?resize=557%2C256&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"List Schemes Initiatives Union Budget 2018-19 Central Govt Tax Senior Citizens\" width=\"557\" height=\"256\" class=\"size-full wp-image-8103\" srcset=\"https://i2.wp.com/sarkariyojana.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/list-schemes-initiatives-union-budget-2018-19-central-govt-8.jpg?w=557&amp;ssl=1 557w, https://i2.wp.com/sarkariyojana.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/list-schemes-initiatives-union-budget-2018-19-central-govt-8.jpg?resize=300%2C138&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 557px) 100vw, 557px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\"/></noscript><p id=\"caption-attachment-8103\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">List Schemes Initiatives Union Budget 2018-19 Central Govt Tax Senior Citizens</p></div><li><b>Other Benefits &#8211; Defense / Technology / Market / Corporate Sector</b> &#8211;<ul><li>Central govt. has increased the budget for defense to Rs. 2.82 lakh crore from previous Rs. 2.67 lakh crore.</li><li>Central govt. has increased the food subsidy to 1.69 lakh crore to 1.4 lakh crore in the previous FY.</li><li>Digital India Scheme has been allocated Rs. 3073 crore.</li><li>Central govt. will set up 5 lakh Wi-Fi networks to benefit 5 crore rural citizens across the country.</li><li>Moreover, govt. has allocated Rs. 7,148 crore  for textile industries.</li><li>Salaries of President is hiked to Rs. 5 lakh, Vice President to Rs. 4 lakh and Governors to Rs. 3.5 lakh.</li><li>Furthermore, there is lower corporate tax on companies with less than Rs. 250 crore turnover in the previous fiscal year.</li></ul></li></ul><p>However, Central govt. has hiked custom duties on Mobiles, Televisions and other electronic items which will result in higher prices.</p><p>Moreover, govt. has also increased import duties on LED / LCD / Crude sunflower seed oil or groundnut oil / sunglasses / cigarette lighters / toys / bus / truck tyres / furniture / watches and footwear which will raise the prices of these items.</p><p>Image Source and Cr